H0.text: Reproduce is what chloroplasts in cells make it possible for the cells to.

H1.text: Hold their rigid shape is made possible by chloroplasts in cells.

H2.text: Absorb and excrete materials is what chloroplasts in cells make possible for the cells to.

H3.text: Carry out photosynthesis is what chloroplasts in cells make possible for the cells.

A5.text: Photosynthesis takes place in organelles called chloroplasts.

A6.text: Chloroplasts have many similarities with photosynthetic bacteria, including a circular chromosome, prokaryotic-type ribosome, and similar proteins in the photosynthetic reaction center.
